<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">
One new subspecies was described (
<bibRefCitation author="Beljaev, EA" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" pagination="55 - 68" refId="B5535761" refString="Beljaev, EA, 2007. Taxonomic changes in the emerald moths (Lepidoptera: Geometridae, Geometrinae) of East Asia, with notes on the systematics and phylogeny of Hemitheini. Zootaxa 1584: 55 - 68" title="Taxonomic changes in the emerald moths (Lepidoptera: Geometridae, Geometrinae) of East Asia, with notes on the systematics and phylogeny of Hemitheini." volume="1584" year="2007">Beljaev 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">
<taxonomicName authority="Matsumura, 1925" authorityName="Matsumura" authorityYear="1925" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Aoshakuna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aoshakuna" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Aoshakuna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1831" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Chlorissa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chlorissa" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Chlorissa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Stephens, but was re-instated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Beljaev, EA" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" pagination="55 - 68" refId="B5535761" refString="Beljaev, EA, 2007. Taxonomic changes in the emerald moths (Lepidoptera: Geometridae, Geometrinae) of East Asia, with notes on the systematics and phylogeny of Hemitheini. Zootaxa 1584: 55 - 68" title="Taxonomic changes in the emerald moths (Lepidoptera: Geometridae, Geometrinae) of East Asia, with notes on the systematics and phylogeny of Hemitheini." volume="1584" year="2007">Beljaev (2007)</bibRefCitation>
. In the same revision, 
<bibRefCitation author="Beljaev, EA" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" pagination="55 - 68" refId="B5535761" refString="Beljaev, EA, 2007. Taxonomic changes in the emerald moths (Lepidoptera: Geometridae, Geometrinae) of East Asia, with notes on the systematics and phylogeny of Hemitheini. Zootaxa 1584: 55 - 68" title="Taxonomic changes in the emerald moths (Lepidoptera: Geometridae, Geometrinae) of East Asia, with notes on the systematics and phylogeny of Hemitheini." volume="1584" year="2007">Beljaev (2007)</bibRefCitation>
subsequently designated 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Inoue" authorityYear="1946" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Nipponogelasma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nipponogelasma" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Nipponogelasma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName genus="Aoshakuna." lsidName="Aoshakuna." pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Aoshakuna.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
As a result of this synonymy, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thierry-Mieg" authorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Nipponogelasma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nipponogelasma lucia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Nipponogelasma lucia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was transferred to 
<taxonomicName authority="Matsumura, 1925" authorityName="Matsumura" authorityYear="1925" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Aoshakuna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aoshakuna" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Aoshakuna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, creating the new combination 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. lucia" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" rank="species" species="lucia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">A. lucia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Beljaev, EA" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" pagination="55 - 68" refId="B5535761" refString="Beljaev, EA, 2007. Taxonomic changes in the emerald moths (Lepidoptera: Geometridae, Geometrinae) of East Asia, with notes on the systematics and phylogeny of Hemitheini. Zootaxa 1584: 55 - 68" title="Taxonomic changes in the emerald moths (Lepidoptera: Geometridae, Geometrinae) of East Asia, with notes on the systematics and phylogeny of Hemitheini." volume="1584" year="2007">Beljaev (2007)</bibRefCitation>
then synonymised this species with 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. sachalinensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" rank="species" species="sachalinensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">A. sachalinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the type species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Matsumura, 1925" authorityName="Matsumura" authorityYear="1925" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Aoshakuna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aoshakuna" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Aoshakuna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
